<span id="freeTextContainer10813893285248210306">A light romantic read by Elizabeth Adler...<br/>It was the first book I read by this author, and I throughly enjoyed it. The setting was beautiful, the characters well-drawn and the events rolled smoothly making this a perfect beach page-turner.<br/>This is the story of Daisy Keane and Harry Montana,when they go on a cruise to Capri to read the will and reveal who is the murderer of Sir Robert Waldo Hardwick, who was a man with money, enemies and a heart of his own.<br/>I shall re-read it in the future.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


